Australian Financial Review journalist Geoff Winestock has spoken out in support of sacked SBS journalist Scott McIntyre . 
  McIntyre was fired on Sunday over his controversial Anzac day tweets . 
  He called Anzac Day 'the cultification of an imperialist invasion' and accused the Diggers of committing war crimes . 
  The AFR writer said he hoped 'in 50 years no soldiers around to honour' SBS Managing Director Michael Ebeid said McIntyre's comments were 'not at all the views of @SBS'